  "prompt": "Does money laundering fall under criminal legislation?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is a criminal offense in most countries and is typically addressed under criminal legislation. Money laundering involves concealing the origins of illegally obtained money by passing it through legitimate businesses or financial systems. Most jurisdictions have specific anti-money laundering (AML) laws that criminalize such activities, with potential penalties including:\n\n1. Criminal prosecution\n2. Substantial fines\n3. Potential imprisonment\n4. Asset seizure\n\nIn many countries, money laundering is considered a serious financial crime with severe legal consequences.",
